a) Java Program to Print Message

Code:
class PrintData {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Compiler design with java");
    }
}

Output : 
Compiler design with java

b) Java Program to get the value from keyboard and print

 Code:.

import java.util.Scanner;
class Input {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.print("Enter an integer: ");
        int number = input.nextInt();
        System.out.println("You entered " + number);
        input.close();
    }
}

Output :

Enter an integer: 10
You entered 10

C) Java Program to add two integer number

Code:


class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    int first = 10;
    int second = 20;
    int sum = first + second;
    System.out.println(first + " + " + second + " = "  + sum);
  }
}

Output :
10 + 20 = 30

d) Java Program to implement Calculator Program

Code:

import java.util.Scanner;
class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    char operator;
    Double number1, number2, result;
    Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);
    System.out.println("Choose an operator: +, -, *, or /");
    operator = input.next().charAt(0);
    System.out.println("Enter first number");
    number1 = input.nextDouble();
    System.out.println("Enter second number");
    number2 = input.nextDouble();
    switch (operator) {
      case '+':
        result = number1 + number2;
        System.out.println(number1 + " + " + number2 + " = " + result);
        break;
      case '-':
        result = number1 - number2;
        System.out.println(number1 + " - " + number2 + " = " + result);
        break;
      case '*':
        result = number1 * number2;
        System.out.println(number1 + " * " + number2 + " = " + result);
        break;
      case '/':
        result = number1 / number2;
        System.out.println(number1 + " / " + number2 + " = " + result);
        break;
      default:
        System.out.println("Invalid operator!");
        break;
    }
    input.close();
  }
}

Output:
Choose an operator: +, -, *, or /
+
Enter first number
10
Enter second number
4
10.0 + 4.0 = 14.0
